main event: An unidentified object, described as an 'S/C' shape, bluish with a green glow, was observed in the sky over Salt Lake City, Utah.
interesting points: The object was observed moving at a high rate of speed, first from east to west, then making a 180-degree turn and moving from west to east.
The object disappeared behind some trees where it was first sighted.
Two jet aircraft were reportedly in the area at the time of the sighting.
The observation lasted only a few seconds.
The report concludes the object was 'Probably Balloon' or 'possibly Astronomical', with 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation'.
sighted object: an 'S/C' shaped object, bluish with a green glow
